
Release 0.3.0:
	* added `captury --verbose` to print some log messages when toggling movie
	  capture, taking screenshot, etc.
	* added explicit cursor drawing support
	* added screenshots hotkey (F10) to produce PNG images of 
	  your current screen
	* output filenames match wine/cedega program names 
	  if wine/cedega is detected.
	* command line tool (captury) has been improved wrt usability.
	* add default config file to @sysconfdir@/captury.conf to be sourced
	  by captury wrapper. you may override its settings via
	  ~/.config/captury.conf

Release 0.1.0 (2007-02-16):
	* initial working version for capturing and encoding video data
